<p> </p>
<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Additional Information</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Ephedrine, pseudoephedrine, methylphenidate, and dextroamphetamine are no longer used to treat nOH because of lack of efficacy and intolerable CNS effects</span></span></span></span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Autonomic Function Testing: Available</span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino"> at 4:15pm Tues, Wed, Thurs NPO 4 hours prior </span></span></span></span></span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Hold oral pressors and antihypertensives 12 hours prior </span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
